cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a new system for emulation of a Full Duplex cellular base station using two spatially separated and coordinated half duplex base stations. The performance of the proposed system is evaluated using a geometric extension of the one-dimensional Wyner model. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory category. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed system involves two base stations coordinating with each other to serve two mobile stations, one in the uplink and one in the downlink. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture category. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper evaluates the performance of the proposed system in terms of energy efficiency and sum-rate. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Multimedia category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed system involves coordination between two base stations to serve two mobile stations. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Systems and Control category. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): There is no explicit mention of cryptography or security in the paper, but the proposed system may have implications for security in wireless networks. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Cryptography and Security category.
